---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Video Interview: Product Vision and Startup Execution | Francisco Cucullu" description="In-depth video interview discussing product vision, market strategy, and startup execution.">
    <article class="wrapper">
        <a href="/blog" class="back">&larr; Back</a>

        <header class="article-header">
            <span class="tag">Interview</span>
            <h1>Video Interview: Product Vision and Startup Execution</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">An in-depth conversation about building products, market strategy, and what it takes to execute as a founder.</p>
            <p class="meta">By Francisco Cucullu &middot; AI Product Leader</p>
        </header>

        <div class="content">
            <p>I sat down for an in-depth video interview covering product vision, market strategy, and startup execution. The conversation went beyond surface-level topics and explored the real challenges of building products that people actually use.</p>

            <div class="video-wrapper">
                <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VAnII-62ry4" title="Video Interview" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>

            <p>We discussed how product vision evolves over time. The initial idea is rarely the one that succeeds. What matters is the ability to listen to users, read the data honestly, and adapt without losing sight of the core problem you set out to solve. Too many founders fall in love with their solution instead of the problem.</p>

            <p>The interview also covered execution. Having a great idea is the easy part. The hard part is shipping consistently, making decisions with incomplete information, and maintaining momentum when things are not going well. These are the skills that separate founders who build lasting companies from those who do not.</p>

            <p>Long-form interviews like this one are valuable because they allow for nuance. A pitch deck gives you three minutes to tell a story. An interview gives you space to explain the reasoning behind your decisions and share the lessons that only come from experience.</p>
        </div>

        <footer class="article-footer">
            <p>Francisco Cucullu is an AI Product Leader building AI products at scale. <a href="/">Learn more</a>.</p>
        </footer>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .wrapper {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    .back {
        color: #a855f7;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .article-header {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .tag {
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
        border-radius: 999rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        background: var(--accent-regular);
        color: var(--accent-text-over);
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: var(--text-3xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .subtitle {
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        color: var(--gray-300);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .meta {
        color: var(--gray-400);
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
    }

    .content {
        color: var(--gray-200);
        line-height: 1.8;
        font-size: var(--text-md);
    }

    .content h2 {
        font-size: var(--text-2xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .content a {
        color: #a855f7;
    }

    .video-wrapper {
        position: relative;
        padding-bottom: 56.25%;
        height: 0;
        overflow: hidden;
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .video-wrapper iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .article-footer {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        padding-top: 2rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
        color: var(--gray-400);
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
    }

    .article-footer a {
        color: #a855f7;
    }

    @media (min-width: 50em) {
        h1 {
            font-size: var(--text-4xl);
        }
    }
</style>
